# Careervexa - MERN Stack Job Board Application 💼

**Careervexa** is a full-stack job board web application that connects job seekers and employers. Users can create profiles, search and apply for jobs, post job listings, and communicate via real-time chat — all built using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express, React, Node.js) with Socket.IO integration for live messaging.

> Built with 💙 as part of a 6-week MERN Full Stack Web Development course project.

---

## 🚀 Tech Stack

### Frontend
- React + Vite
- TailwindCSS
- Axios
- React Router
- React Toastify

### Backend
- Node.js + Express.js
- MongoDB + Mongoose
- JWT Authentication
- Socket.IO

### Real-Time Chat
- One-on-one messaging
- Typing indicators
- Delivered & Read ticks (like WhatsApp)
- Unread message count
- Media upload preview

---

## ✨ Key Features

- 👤 User Signup/Login with role-based access (admin/user)
- 🧾 Post and view job listings
- 💬 Real-time chat between users
- 🔍 Search users by name/email to start conversations
- 📄 View and edit user profiles
- 🛡️ Protected routes using JWT
- 📱 Fully responsive design

---

## 📁 Folder Structure

careervexa/
├── client/ # Frontend - React
├── server/ # Backend - Node.js & Express
├── .gitignore
└── README.md

## ⚙️ Getting Started (Run Locally)

### 1. Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/your-username/careervexa.git
cd careervexa

## Set Up Frontend
cd client
npm install

Create a .env file inside the client/ folder:
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000/api


## Run the frontend:
npm run dev


## Set Up Backend
cd ../server
npm install


Create a .env file inside the server/ folder:

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret

## Run the backend:
npm run dev

## Access the App
Frontend: http://localhost:5173
Backend API: http://localhost:5000/api

🌐 Deployment 
Frontend: Deploy to Vercel
Backend: Deploy to Render or Railway
Update environment variables accordingly on deployed platforms.

